    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels at MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements. Validation results demonstrate RH < 1 at worst-case operating condition with discretization error below 5% GCI threshold. The model is considered credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device within the defined COU. Note: aleatory uncertainty in the RH index validation result (VR-01) was characterised qualitatively via literature review of red blood cell fragility variability; a structured probabilistic UQ was not performed for this result.",
